<% content_for :title, "Studio Agreement — Admin Manual" %>

<div class="flex gap-8 lg:gap-12">
  <aside class="hidden lg:block w-52 flex-shrink-0">
    <%= render "sidebar" %>
  </aside>

  <article class="min-w-0 flex-1">
    <%= render BreadcrumbComponent.new(items: [
      { label: "Admin Manual", path: admin_docs_path },
      { label: "Agreement", path: nil }
    ]) %>

    <h1 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-stone-900">Studio Agreement</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-stone-500">The terms customers accept at checkout — and how versioning protects you.</p>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-stone-700">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">What the Agreement Does</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            Every customer must accept the current Studio Agreement before completing a booking.
            It's a required step — the <strong>Confirm & Pay</strong> button is disabled until they
            check the acceptance box. The agreement covers studio rules, conduct expectations,
            liability, and payment policies.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Publishing a New Version</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            Go to <strong>Agreement → Edit</strong>. Write or update your terms using the rich text
            editor (supports bold, italic, headings, bullet lists, and links). Click
            <strong>Publish New Version</strong> to make it live immediately.
          </p>
          <p>
            Each saved version is automatically numbered. Future bookings will use the new version.
            Past bookings remain linked to the version the customer originally agreed to — this
            protects you legally if terms change after a booking is made.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Agreement History</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            All previous versions are stored and remain viewable at any time from the Agreement page.
            You can see exactly what a customer agreed to at the time of their booking by viewing the
            booking detail — it links to the specific agreement version they accepted.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-stone-900">Before Going Live</h2>
        <div class="mt-3 text-sm">
          <p>
            You must publish at least one agreement version before customers can complete a booking.
            If no agreement exists, the checkout page will not allow them to proceed. Set this up
            before you create any public slots.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</div>
